    "discriminators": [
     "THE textbook DSP signature of this whole ontology: a HARMONIC COMB LOCKED TO THE MAINS. f0 sits at the line frequency (50 Hz in EU/AU, 60 Hz in NA) or its first even multiple (100/120 Hz, from full-wave rectification and from transformer core magnetostriction, which flexes twice per cycle), with many integer partials stacked above it.",
     "Diagnostic conjunction: pitch_hz in 50-120 Hz AND harmonicity > 0.6 AND spectral_flatness < 0.2 AND high partial_count AND near-zero spectral_flux AND high stationarity. Nothing else in ELECTRICITY looks remotely like this.",
     "Against ELECArc and COMStatic: those are noise (flatness > 0.4, harmonicity < 0.3). BUZZ is the tonal pole of the same category — the flatness/harmonicity axis alone separates them with enormous margin.",
     "Against ELECSprk and ELECZap: those are event trains built of transients. A hum has essentially NO onsets; spectral_flux near zero is the test.",
     "Against MOTRElec and DSGNDron: a motor's comb WANDERS with load and a designed drone MOVES; mains hum is rock-stable in pitch across the whole file. Text (transformer, ground, pickup, amp, substation) commits the call.",
     "A guitar-pickup or ground hum is a BUZZ rather than a pure hum: same comb, but with far more upper-partial energy, so spectral_centroid and partial_count run higher. Still ELECBuzz."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "ELECArc",
     "ELECMisc",
     "MOTRElec",
     "DSGNDron",
     "COMStatic"
    ]
