    "discriminators": [
     "PROVENANCE, NOT SOUND. ELECEmf is defined by the TRANSDUCER — UCS says 'electromagnetic field recordings SPECIFICALLY' — and not by any acoustic property whatsoever. An EMF recording of a CRT, a hard drive, a phone handshake and a power line share nothing in feature space; the only thing they share is an induction coil in front of them instead of a microphone.",
     "Consequence: NEVER assert this from signal. Its content routinely mimics ELECBuzz (a mains comb), COMStatic, UIData or UIGlitch, and no DSP feature can reveal that the pickup was a coil. The tier sets alpha = 0, so the priors below cannot move the posterior; they are documentary only.",
     "Decide entirely on text: 'EMF', 'coil', 'induction', 'pickup', 'field', 'radiation'.",
