    "discriminators": [
     "SHORT, SHOCKING, FAST, PERCUSSIVE — UCS's own four words, and every one of them is a DSP statement: sub-10 ms attack, high crest factor, front-loaded envelope (low envelope_temporal_centroid, high envelope_skewness), negligible sustain.",
     "The REPETITION clause matters as much as the impulse clause, and it is the reason this signature is not simply 'impulsive'. UCS: 'Or a repetition of short fast sounds. A taser is a series of ZAPS.' So a ZAP file may legitimately contain a PULSE TRAIN — transient_count > 1 does NOT disqualify it, and a gate on transient_count would be flat wrong here.",
